LEADERSHIP : Turkey’s ruling AK Party has lost control of Istanbul after a re-run of the city’s mayoral election, delivering a stinging blow to President Erdogan. With nearly all ballots counted, main opposition party candidate Ekrem Imamoglu had a lead of 775,000 votes, a huge increase on the margin of 13,000 he achieved in the earlier election. […] The post Erdogan’s Party Suffers Blow After Istanbul Re-Run Poll Defeat appeared first on Leadership Newspaper and NNN. Source: Leadership News